<apex:page controller="datahugapps.DatahugController">

	<apex:includeScript value="{!URLFOR($Resource.datahugapps__datahug, 'jquery.min.js')}" />
	<apex:includeScript value="{!URLFOR($Resource.datahugapps__datahug, 'admin-util.js')}" />
	<apex:stylesheet value="{!URLFOR($Resource.datahugapps__datahug, 'main.css')}" />
<div id="tabs">
	<div id ="datahugAdminLoading" style="padding: 40px; text-align: center;">
		<apex:image url="{!URLFOR($Resource.datahugapps__datahug, 'images/ui-anim_basic_16x16.gif')}"  width="16" height="16"/>
	</div>
	<div id ="datahugNonAdmin" style="display:none;">
		<div class="message"><h3>You do not have permission to edit Datahug Settings. Please contact your System Administrator.</h3></div>
	</div>
	<div id="datahugAdmin" style="display:none;">
	<div class="datahugSettings message" style="display:none;"><h3></h3></div>
		<apex:pageBlock >
			<div id="datahugCreds" class="datahugSection">
				<apex:pageblockSection columns="1" title="Datahug Token/Secret">
				<div class="message" style="display:none;"><h3></h3></div>
				<div>
				<p>API token and secret pairs can be generated by a Datahug user with administrative rights from the <a href="https://apps.datahug.com/Settings#tabs-ApiCredentials" target="_blank"><strong>Settings > Advanced > API Credentials > Add</strong></a> page in Datahug.</p>  	
					<table class="list">
			            <tr class="dataRow">
							<td class="labelCol quarter align-right" colspan="1">Token</td>
							<td class="" colspan="1"><input id="cred-token" type="text" value=""/></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol quarter align-right" colspan="1">Secret</td>
							<td class="" colspan="1"><input id="cred-secret" type="password" value=""/></td>
						</tr>
					</table>	
					<div class="button-holder">
						<span id="cred-settings-save" class="btn disabled">Save</span>
						<span class="load"></span>
					</div>	        
				</div>
				</apex:pageblockSection>		
			</div>

		
			<div id="datahugSync" class="datahugSection">
				<apex:pageblockSection columns="1" title="Datahug Sync to Salesforce Settings" >
					<div class="message" style="display:none;"><h3></h3></div>
					<p>Datahug syncs information such as last inbound/outbound interactions and next meeting to Salesforce Leads, Contacts, Accounts and Opportunities. Datahug also automatically creates Contacts in Salesforce for selected Accounts once they are above a HugRank threshold.</p>	
					<table class="list">
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left" colspan="2">1. Log into Datahug to grant access to sync Datahug information to Salesforce. Go to: <a href="https://apps.datahug.com/Settings#tabs-ConnectToSF" target="_blank">Settings > Advanced > Configure Salesforce</a></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left">2. Set your daily API limit</td>
							<td class=""><input id="api-limit" type="text" value="" style="text-align:center;"/><br/><span class="small">Leave blank for no limit</span></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left">3. Automatically create Contacts in Salesforce where the HugRank is over:<br/><span class="small">The 'Auto-Create Contacts' checkbox on an Account must be checked before Contacts will be automatically created for that Account</span></td>
							<td class=""><input id="hugrank-limit" type="text" value="" style="text-align:center;" /><br/><span class="small">Leave blank for default value of 40</span></td>
						</tr>
					</table>	
					<div class="button-holder">
						<span id="sf-settings-save" class="btn enabled">Save</span>
						<span class="load"></span>
					</div>				
					
				</apex:pageblockSection>
				
				
			</div>
		
			<div id="dhTabStates" class="datahugSection">
				<apex:pageblockSection columns="1" title="Customize Tabs" >
					<div class="message" style="display:none;"><h3></h3></div>
					<p>Choose what tabs to show and hide within the Datahug Application.</p>	
					<table class="list">
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left">Activity</td>
							<td class=""><input id="activity" type="checkbox"/></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left">Analytics</td>
							<td class=""><input id="analytics" type="checkbox"/></td>
						</tr>
					</table>	
					<div class="button-holder">
						<span id="tab-settings-save" class="btn enabled">Save</span>
						<span class="load"></span>
					</div>
					

				</apex:pageblockSection>
				
				
			</div>
	
			<div id="chatterSetting" class="datahugSection">
				<apex:pageblockSection columns="1" title="Chatter Integration" >
					<div class="message" style="display:none;"><h3></h3></div>
					<p>Choose whether or not Chatter integration is enabled within the Datahug Application.</p> 
					<table class="list">
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left">Enable Chatter</td>
							<td><input id="chatter" type="checkbox"/></td>
						</tr>
					</table>					
					<div class="button-holder">
						<span id="chatter-settings-save" class="btn enabled">Save</span>
						<span class="load"></span>
					</div>
				</apex:pageblockSection>
				
				
			</div>
			
			<div id="validationSetting" class="datahugSection">
				<apex:pageblockSection columns="1" title="'Add as Contact' button" >
					<div class="message" style="display:none;"><h3></h3></div>
					<div>
						<p>The One Click 'Add as Contact' feature allows users to quickly add Contacts to Salesforce. <br/>
						Disable One Click 'Add as Contact' if your organisation has: </p>
						<ul> <li>Complex validation rules</li><li>Required fields</li><li>Prefer users to have an opportunity to complete the Contact form before adding</li></ul>
					</div>	
					<table class="list">
						<tr>
							<td class="labelCol align-left">Enable One Click 'Add as Contact' button</td>
							<td><input id="validation" type="checkbox"/></td>
							</tr>
						</table>
						<div class="button-holder">
							<span id="validation-settings-save" class="btn enabled">Save</span>
							<span class="load"></span>
						</div>					
					</apex:pageblockSection>	
				</div>
					  
		</apex:pageBlock>
	</div>
</div>
</apex:page>